                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Heh, here's an interesting story from last night. A group of friends were going up to hate to farm Marsinger pieces. A 65 enchanter was already going, so I asked if I could bring my 52 cleric along, since she could use the exp and some of the old hate armor was still considered an upgrade. They said sure. So the group of us went up. 65 monk, 65 cleric, 64 wizard, 65 enchanter, 56 Warrior and myself...the baby. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Well, we were up there for a while, got some decent drops, and I noticed some wierd things from this enchanter. We were killing in tier 1 mainly, and he was using bliss to mez. Well, he was still mezzing, but that's not exactly the most efficient mez, especially considering no mob in PoHate is over level 64, save for Maestro and Inny. A few other things caught my attention, but I didn't say anything. He did alright regardless.
<br />

<br />
So, monk later tells us hand of maestro is up, and we decide to kill it for the warrior since he doesn't have that yet. Plan was, warrior runs in, and parks himself in the corner, everyone else comes in afterward and gets behind hand. Typical strategy when dealing AEing mobs, and hand has an AE lifetap for about 350 I believe. So, everything goes fin until all of sudden, at about 80%, Hand starts agroing everyone *but* the warrior. I thought this was odd. For the rest of the fight, we're ping ponging him. I can't figure out why this would happen, except if people were over agroing. But, everyone over agroing? Was just weird. So I scroll up, and I see it...
<br />

<br />
"Hand of Maestro blinks a few times."
<br />

<br />
The enchanter mem blurred Hand to take agro off himself! In the process, he killed the agro on the warrior, and almost got the poor wizard killed! Not to mention everyone else needing mad spot heals from the AE. I talked to him later and asked why he mem blurred Hand. He told me it was to get agro off him. I then asked him, "Don't you have boggle?" He simply replied, "What's boggle do?" I couldn't believe it...a 65 enchanter, with, as he said, over 60 AAs, doesn't know what boggle does. I couldn't believe it...</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><center>Sage Fadarm
<br />
