                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">He'd of even been better off just getting off a couple stuns while the MA reagained aggro (although I don't know if the Maestro is stunnable). You might suggest to him if he is hell-bent on using a blur in the middle of fights, that he use Reoccuring Amnesia (lvl 49) a single target, non-ae 25% mem-blur every six seconds. More than sufficient for Hate.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Remember, if you found that 25% thing in Lucy (or some other spell parser) it doesn't mean it wipes 25% of the list, it's more along the lines of a 25% chance to completely wipe the list. This isn't completely true. From what I understand, it's more of an arbitrary number. Higher the %, greater chance of completely wiping the hate list. That spell can still very much screw the agro of your group. Memblurs have their uses, but should rarely (if ever) be used in a fight.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">one of these...sure reasonable..4?!?! sounds like an idiot to me really heh 
<br />

<br />
MAKE him understand why blur is bad ..you should take some initiative and explain further.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I tried, I really did. But he just didn't get it. I told him that the reason people are over agroing is because he was resetting the hate list. That means all the agro the warrior was building up was null, and when the wizard lands his 2k nuke afterwards, he's dead. *shrugs* I won't ever group with him, but that's easy since I rarely play with other enchanters as my enchanter, and, he's 65 and my cleric is only 52. If I ever have the opportunity to group with him, I will simply decline.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><center>Sage Fadarm
